Mapfre in Talks to Sell 49% Stake in Banking Unit to Caja Madrid

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-03-06T11:34:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-06/mapfre-in-talks-to-sell-49-stake-in-banking-unit-to-caja-madrid.html
  Mapfre SA (MAP)  is in “very advanced
talks” with Caja  Madrid  over the sale of its 49 percent stake
in a banking business run by the two companies, Caja Madrid said
in a regulatory filing.  Mapfre will sell its stake in Banco de Servicios
Financieros Caja-Madrid Mapfre and acquire the lender’s 12.5
percent stake in Mapfre Internacional, the filing said. It
didn’t say what the terms of the deal will be.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Sills in Madrid at   bsills@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net  